State-owned enterprises and advantageous private enterprises have entered the old revolutionary area of Gannan.
From September 26th to 27th, in order to deepen and expand the educational achievements of the theme of "do not forget the original intention and remember the mission", the Central Military-civilian Integration Office, the National Defense Science and Industry Bureau, and the National Federation of Industry and Commerce jointly organized the research activities of "state-owned enterprises and advantageous private enterprises into the old revolutionary area of Gannan", revisited the revolutionary history, pursued the red footprint, inherited the red gene, and carried out the needs of relevant enterprises and Ganzhou City to promote the accelerated development of the old revolutionary area.
Jin Zhuanglong, executive deputy director of the Central Military-Civilian Integration Office, Xu Lejiang, Deputy Minister of the Central United Front, Party Secretary of the All-China Federation of Industry and Commerce, Executive Vice Chairman Xu Lejiang, Zhang Kejun, Director of the National Defense Science and Industry Bureau, Deputy Secretary of the Jiangxi Provincial Party Committee, Li Bingjun, Secretary of the Ganzhou Municipal Party Committee, participated in the research.
The enterprises participating in the research activities include China Aerospace Science and Technology Group Co., Ltd. and other 8 military industrial group companies, Hunan rare earth metal materials research institute and other 10 people's mouth state-owned enterprises, Singxiang Group and other 15 advantageous private enterprises.
During this period, the researchers visited the commemorative park of the departure site of the Long March of the Central Red Army, remembered the revolutionary martyrs, received the revolutionary traditional education, reviewed the difficult history of the Long March period of the Red Army, investigated 7 enterprises and a testing center in Ganzhou City, held a special symposium, and reached 8 cooperation projects and signed on-site contracts.
At the symposium of research activities, Ganzhou City introduced its unique industrial advantages and introduced high-quality projects to participating enterprises.
China National Armored Industry Group Co., Ltd., China Steel Research Technology Group Co., Ltd., Xi'an Tianhe Defense Technology Co., Ltd., Jiangxi Jinli Permanent Magnet Technology Co., Ltd., speaking on behalf of Military Industry Group Corporation, Minkou State-owned Enterprises, Private Enterprises, and Local Enterprises respectively, said that it will continue to strengthen the demand docking work between state-owned enterprises, advantageous private enterprises and Jiangxi Province and Ganzhou City, gradually broaden the field of cooperation, help industrial transformation and upgrading, and promote high-quality development in the old revolutionary area.
Through this research activity, we have further understood the unique industrial development advantages of Gannan Revolutionary Old District, clarified the key tasks of the economic and social development of the old revolutionary area at this stage, strengthened the belief of state-owned and private enterprises to serve the people and entrepreneurship, and played an important role in promoting the transformation mode, structural adjustment and people's livelihood of Gannanyuan Central Soviet District, promoting the quality change, efficiency change and power change of economic development.
Beijing market supervision department before the festival to carry out comprehensive law enforcement commodity prices are basically stable
Beijing, September 27 (Reporter Du Yan) In order to strengthen the pre-holiday market supervision and law enforcement, the Beijing Municipal Market Supervision Bureau inspected more than 2,000 households of various business entities on the eve of the National Day.
The inspection shows that the market sales of grain and oil, meat, fruits, vegetables, egg milk and other necessities of life supply is sufficient, commodity prices are basically stable, no serious violations of the law have been found, and the market operation order is generally stable.
Today, the reporter learned from the Beijing Municipal Bureau of Market Supervision that the Bureau carried out "comprehensive law enforcement inspection day" activities in the city, focusing on price, industry and commerce, quality supervision, food and medicine, commerce and other elements, all aspects of law enforcement inspection, comprehensive regulation of market operation order.
According to reports, the Beijing Municipal Market Supervision Bureau price, industry and commerce, quality supervision, food and medicine, business and other five law enforcement teams to work together, close cooperation, by the heads of law enforcement agencies led by the team, grouped on the random extraction of some business entities for joint law enforcement inspection.
During the inspection, law enforcement officials focused on checking the price behavior, advertising, food safety, measurement standards, and production safety systems.
The market supervision bureaus of each district have also organized joint law enforcement inspections, dispatched more than 1,600 law enforcement personnel, inspected more than 2,000 households of various business entities, and the inspection showed that the supply of daily necessities such as grain and oil, meat, fruits, vegetables, and egg milk sold in the market was sufficient, the commodity prices were basically stable, the operators were able to abide by the law, and the market operation order was generally stable.
The Beijing Municipal Bureau of Market Supervision said that during the National Day, it will strengthen emergency duty, continue to carry out inspections and inspections of the market, quickly deal with various market supervision issues in accordance with the law, and conduct business violations reflected by the public, once verified, will be seriously dealt with in accordance with the law, and effectively safeguard the legitimate rights and interests of consumers.
Confucius Institute of the Royal Cambodian Academy of Sciences "China in My Heart" Chinese Essay Contest Announced
The "China in My Heart" Chinese essay contest with the theme of the 70th anniversary of New China was announced and awarded ceremony was held at the Confucius Institute of the Royal Cambodian Academy of Sciences on the 26th.
Chinese Embassy diplomats Zhong Qifa, representatives of the Cambodian-Chinese Council, and Wei Siyu, president of the Jiangxi Chamber of Commerce in Cambodia, presented awards to the award-winning guests.
According to the Chinese director of the Confucius Institute at the Royal Academy of Sciences of Cambodia, the competition lasted for two months and was attended by Cambodian primary school students, secondary school students (including specialtizers) and university students (including social personnel).
The Chinese Embassy in Cambodia diplomat Zhong Shufa issued the award certificate for Lin Weicai, winner of the first prize of the university group, and Guo Lina, winner of the first prize of the primary and secondary school group.
Chai Keqing said that the entries are carried out separately according to the university group and the primary and secondary school group, inviting the judging committee of senior Chinese experts in Cambodia to finally select the first prize of the university group, 2 second prizes, 3 third prizes, 10 excellent awards; 1 first prize, 5 second prize, 10 third prize, and 20 excellent awards in the primary and secondary school group.
Lin Weicai, the first prize winner of the university group, said that he has been learning Chinese for 15 years and has had a huge impact on himself.
Through the essay contest, it is to describe the well-being brought to Cambodia under the "Belt and Road" and the traditional friendship between China and Cambodia, and hope that the younger generation will continue to contribute to the friendship between China and Cambodia.
Guests and award-winning players.
Guo Lina, winner of the first prize of the primary and secondary school group, said that as an overseas Chinese, she had the opportunity to express the emotion of "China in his heart" and won the award through the words of her native country, and she had a different excitement.
Organizers said that through the competition, not only created a positive atmosphere of China-Cambodia relations, but also attracted more and more Cambodian students to learn Chinese and study in China.
The United Nations International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) released a report on the 26th, saying that Iran has begun to use advanced centrifuges to accelerate the production of enriched uranium, further violating the nuclear agreement with world powers in 2015.
The IAEA report said that advanced centrifuges at Iran's Natanz Nuclear Facility "are accumulating or are ready to accumulate enriched uranium."
Since U.S. President Donald Trump withdrew from the nuclear deal in May last year and imposed sanctions on Iran, Iran is gradually violating the restrictions of the 2015 nuclear deal with major powers.
The agreement stipulates that Iran can only use the first generation of IR-1 centrifuges to refine uranium.
Other signatories to the deal, Britain, China, France, Germany and Russia, have been trying to salvage the deal, but Tehran has repeatedly accused Europe of not doing enough.
According to Japan's Kyodo News Agency, on the afternoon of the 25th local time, Japanese Foreign Minister Motegi Minchong held talks with Russian Foreign Minister Lavrov in New York, the United States, and confirmed that it will promote the conclusion and negotiation of a peace treaty including the territorial issue of the four northern islands (Japan-Russia disputed islands, Japan said "the four northern islands", and the Russian said "South Kuril Islands"), and develop bilateral relations in a wide range of political, economic and other fields.
This is the first consultation with Russia after Motegi took office as foreign minister and was the head of the negotiation of a peace treaty.
Mogi told the Russian side that it hopes to carry out consultations, including promoting common economic activities (on the four northern islands).
According to the Japanese government, the talks did not discuss the territorial issue in detail.
At the Japan-Russia summit in December 2018, the foreign ministers of the two countries were confirmed as the leaders of the two countries to accelerate the negotiation policy.
At the meeting, the foreign ministers of the two countries welcomed the progress of consultations on common economic activities in the fields of tourism and garbage disposal.
Mogi said that it is expected to implement the tourism pilot business in October: "I hope to successfully implement it and promote the next step."
In addition, the talks confirmed that Lavrov will cooperate with the G20 foreign ministers' meeting in Nagoya in November.
Tuionetoa was elected as Tonga’s new prime minister.
The Parliament of Tonga, a South Pacific island nation, on the 27th, elected the current Minister of Finance and National Planning, Poshiva Tuionetoa, as Tonga's new Prime Minister, replacing former Prime Minister Akilisi Pohiva, who died of illness earlier this month.
According to the website of Tonga's main media outlet, MATANGI, the Tongan Parliament is unicameral and consists of 26 members.
In the parliamentary vote on the same day, Tuionetoa won 23 votes to defeat the rival deputy prime minister and minister of infrastructure and tourism, Semici Sika, and was successfully elected.
Tonga is a constitutional monarchy, with a system of separation of executive, legislative and judicial powers.
Tuionetoa was also required to accept the king's appointment.
The next parliamentary elections for Tonga will be held in 2021.
