Garbage classification education first into Jilin kindergarten environmental protection concept from the doll to catch up
On the 27th, a kindergarten in Jilin City, Jilin Province, carried out garbage classification education classes to teach young children to distinguish recyclable garbage and other categories of garbage.
It is reported that this is the first time that garbage classification has entered the local early childhood education classroom.
A few days ago, nine departments of Jilin Province jointly issued the "Jilin Province to promote the prefecture-level municipal domestic waste classification and treatment work plan."
In 2019, on the basis of the pilot of compulsory classification of domestic waste in Changchun, the province decided to carry out the classification of domestic waste in prefecture-level cities.
Jilin City is one of them.
We hope that through this event, we can realize the effect of promoting the family with young children and the society driven by kindergarten, and advocate the concept of environmental protection.
Liu Lijuan, executive director of the Hi Faner International Kindergarten, who held the event, said.
On the same day, the director read out the environmental initiative, hoping that the garbage classification should start from the children.
After performing the "Low Carbon Babe" dance, the children started a small game of garbage classification.
The instructor also issued “recyclable” and “other garbage” labels, advising children to go home and glue the label to the trash can and record small videos.
Liu Lijuan introduced that the kindergarten has always advocated the concept of low-carbon and green environmental protection, and regularly opened an environmental protection lecture hall.
In the park, a cortable garbage can is also set up at the garbage delivery site, which is marked with the category of delivery.
Teacher teaches children what can be recycled garbage 苍雁 摄
According to preliminary statistics, the amount of municipal domestic waste generated in Jilin Province in 2018 was about 5.4652 million tons, all of which entered the domestic waste disposal site for processing.
Among them, sanitary landfills 3,292,900 tons, incineration of 2.0923 million tons, and comprehensive utilization process 80,100 tons.
After years of efforts, all cities and counties in the province have the ability to deal with domestic waste harmlessly.
In the "Jilin Province to promote the classification and treatment of prefecture-level urban domestic waste", it is explicitly required to carry out in-depth activities such as garbage classification into the campus, textbooks, and classrooms, and strengthen the interaction between students and parents by creating garbage classification songs, songs, cartoons, micro-videos, etc., so as to achieve the effect of "educating a child, affecting a family, driving a community, and cultivating a new generation of people".
