Chirac's death The legacy of politics
On the 26th local time, former French President Jacques Chirac died at the age of 86.
At a time when the world is in a century of unprecedented changes, the French politician's many political legacies left in power still deserve our praise.
Chirac served as president of France for 12 years in a very charismatic way.
He inherited the spirit of independence and autonomy of the Gaullism, but also firmly supported European integration, and was the representative of the pursuit of the "European dream".
At the same time, he also vigorously advocated the world's multipolarity and multilateralism, and is a politician with a strategic vision.
That is why the French media described him as "an outstanding representative of France on the world stage".
One of Chirac’s relishing political decisions was his opposition to the U.S.-led war in Iraq.
Under his leadership, France and Germany have withstanded the pressure of the United States and are at the forefront of the anti-war.
A year after the outbreak of the war, he predicted that the war in Iraq would lead to increased terrorist activities and make the world more dangerous.
Later, it turned out that Chirac’s warning was quite correct.
In the current situation of European integration, the unilateralism of the United States is becoming more and more prominent, and Chirac is pursuing the past, Chirac's strategic thinking and choice of international politics and global affairs undoubtedly has strong inspirational significance.
Chirac is also a French politician who makes the Chinese feel familiar and kind.
He is one of the advocates and creators of the "Golden Decade" of China-France relations, and after being elected as the French president for the first time in 1995, he promoted the rapid development of China-France relations with the strategic vision of politicians.
In 2004, China and France established a comprehensive strategic partnership, and bilateral exchanges between China and France entered a new stage.
During the Chirac administration, bilateral trade between China and France grew rapidly, and the cooperation between the two countries in various fields such as aviation, nuclear energy and railway transportation has made breakthrough progress.
The year of Chinese-French culture initiated by Chirac has created a new model of cultural exchange in the history of China and France.
Chirac’s lifelong love for Chinese culture was particularly impressive.
It is understood that his Chinese diplomats introduced that Chirac can carry some of the poems of Li Bai and Du Fu, and even accurately judge the historical era of Chinese bronzes.
"It doesn't really go to Egypt without looking at the pyramids, and it's not really going to China without looking at Qin Jun." - This golden sentence comes from Chirac.
In an interview with Xinhua News Agency, Chirac said: "The West has concerns about China's political and social development, the ecological problems caused by China's economic growth, and China's political position in the international arena.
But I have full confidence in China.
I think China is a country with a long history of civilization, and its experience is enough to help it build the concept and values for harmonious development and assume its responsibilities on the world stage for a long time.”
I also believe that China's rejuvenation will bring new creative vitality to world culture and enrich world culture.
The S. is gone, but the political legacy and revelations that Chirac has left to the world will live on.
