Formed Members of the Legislative Council of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region Jointly Representatives Against the US-related Hong Kong Bill
Some members of the Hong Kong Legislative Council issued a joint statement on the 27th, expressing strong opposition to the adoption of the Hong Kong Human Rights and Democracy Act of 2019 by the Foreign Affairs Committee of the Senate and the House of Representatives of the United States Congress.
The statement, signed by 40 formed lawmakers, said that at present, Hong Kong's rights are granted by the Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, including maintaining the status of a free trade port and a separate customs territory, signing and implementing bilateral and multilateral agreements in the name of "Hong Kong, China" in different fields, such as economy, finance, shipping, trade, communications, tourism, culture, sports, etc., and the trade, cooperation and development relations between different countries and regions around the world.
These rights are not given by any foreign government or legislature.
Hong Kong has always strictly abided by international agreements, international rules, laws and business ethics, and has participated in many related fields of cooperation with different countries and regions, and has achieved remarkable results and is obvious to all.
The statement said that the move by the Foreign Affairs Committee of the Senate and the House of Representatives of the United States to pass the relevant bill is not necessary, but in response to the call of its agents who are evil, as a means of grossly interfering in Hong Kong's internal affairs and fighting for political leverage for its agents in Hong Kong.
The establishment lawmakers deeply regret the US meeting and strongly oppose it.
Hong Kong is an important trading partner of the United States and the source of the largest trade surplus.
Hong Kong's excellent rule of law, fair and free business environment, and an incorruptible society make it a good location for American businessmen to do business.
If the United States adopts this bill, in addition to cracking down on the interests of Hong Kong and the United States itself, it will make Sino-US relations worse, and have no benefit, and harm others.
The statement said that Hong Kong will, as always, unswervingly implement the "one country, two systems" policy, continue to enjoy the rights granted by the Basic Law, and earnestly fulfill its obligations.
Whether in the past, present or future, Hong Kong will continue to make its due contribution to the international community and international trade.
According to the European Times on the 26th, the two houses of the French parliament will discuss immigration policy reform next week.
French President Emmanuel Macron recently said that France cannot "accept everyone", but at the same time, it must strive to "accept it properly".
Macron is trying to find a compromise on immigration to slow the upcoming debate.
Recently, Macron said in an interview during the general debate of the UN General Assembly in New York, the United States, that he hoped to have a real "two-pronged" plan on immigration policy to find a balance between humanitarianism and efficiency.
“If France wants to be able to properly accept (immigraters), it cannot accept everyone,” Macron said.
Macron cites four priorities in immigration policy: granting asylum status to refugees in need of protection as soon as possible; promoting the integration of migrants more efficiently; receiving and protecting all migrants entering French territory; and more efficient resettlement of people who enter France illegally and are not suitable for staying.
Whether illegal immigrants should be protected by the “National Medical Assistance” (AME) system is the most discussed topic in the past.
Macron said he wanted to "evaluate" the system, but did not remove it, but imposed some restrictions.
After Macron's remarks, Le Pen, the leader of the far-right "National Alliance", tweeted that Macron's statement was "empty talk".
Rascher, a member of the right-wing Republican Party and president of the Senate, also said that immigration policy should be discussed in a "de-escalation" but "face to reality" way, and Macron should be indirectly criticized.
On immigration, France should be “more and better” and criticized Macron for “manufacting” the issue.
The new asylum and immigration law, which has been in place for a year, has led to differences of opinion within the ruling party, but at the same time it has not been able to appease the right-wing opposition.
In the next 2022 election, the topic of immigration policy will once again be the focus of far-right attacks, and Macron needs to make a difference on this issue, but it will also risk angering the ruling party's inner leftists.
According to reports, the lower house of the French National Assembly will debate immigration policy from September 30, and the Senate will debate from October 2.
There are signs that China's A-shares are ushering in a "repurchase tide", and many listed companies have come up with "real money and silver" to buy back the company's shares.
According to the statistics of Oriental Wealth, a financial data service provider, as of the 27th, the total amount of repurchase implementation of A-share listed companies in 2019 has exceeded 100 billion yuan (RMB, the same below), far exceeding the data of the same period of previous years, setting a record high in the amount of A-share share repurchase funds.
In this regard, Xu Yang, chairman of Shanghai Mai Kerong Information Consulting Co., Ltd., said that the overall valuation of the A-share market this year is low, and the repurchase of shares at a relatively low price is conducive to the efficiency of the use of funds by listed companies, and also reflects the willingness of listed companies to actively manage market value and abundant cash flow, which is conducive to boosting investor confidence.
In addition, the continuous improvement of the share repurchase system has also promoted listed companies to actively carry out share repurchases.
For example, at the beginning of this year, the Shanghai Stock Exchange and the Shenzhen Stock Exchange issued the implementation rules for the repurchase of shares by listed companies, providing detailed stock repurchase standards and guidelines for listed companies.
According to media statistics, since this year, listed companies that have implemented an increase in repurchase plans have mainly focused on the infrastructure industry, real estate industry, information technology industry and electronic equipment manufacturing industry.
In addition, from the perspective of the amount of repurchase payment, the repurchase amount of six listed companies this year exceeded 1 billion yuan.
Among them, the first place is Yili shares, whose repurchase amount is more than 5 billion yuan.
How will the repurchase of shares of listed companies affect the market?
Zhao Xijun, vice president of the School of Finance and Finance of Renmin University of China, said in an interview with the China News Agency that on the one hand, the repurchase shows that the listed company has strong economic strength and good financial situation, and has the ability to maintain the stability of the stock price and give investors confidence; on the other hand, it also shows that the listed company and its controlling shareholders are responsible for the company, the market is responsible for the consideration of investors.
The former is based on the company's good business performance, while the latter requires listed companies and their controlling shareholders to have high quality.
For the capital market, these are the core basic elements.
Repurchased shares by listed companies is conducive to boosting investor confidence and supporting the stock prices of listed companies.
In addition, according to the Oriental Securities Research Report, according to the expected number of share repurchases set by A-share listed companies as a whole since the beginning of this year, and the average price of shares that have been repurchased, the incremental funds brought by the repurchased shares for the A-share market this year are expected to exceed 150 billion yuan.
In the past two months, the restoration of the large-scale mural "Tiantian Sanctation Map" of Tianjin Tiangong, a key national cultural protection unit, was announced on the 26th, and will be reopened to the public during the National Day this year.
The "Sand of the Day" is a large-scale traditional mural that fully reflects the life of Mazu.
With the approval of the relevant state departments, Cai Changkui, director of the former Tianjin Civic Museum (Tianguo Palace), was drawn from 1991 to 1994.
It is understood that this mural is painted on the south and north palace walls of the Tiangong main hall, with a total length of 32 meters and a height of 2.6 meters, divided into two parts, with more than 30 stories such as the birth of the day, the sea crossing, and the Ascension of Yuhua, and the 358 characters reproduce the life and deeds of Mazu.
Cai Changkui said that in recent years, Tianjin summer rain, dry winter, this "wet and dry" led to the rubble of the murals, the rupture part of the total mural area of 60%.
In order to protect and rescue the murals of the Mazu deeds, the Ancient Cultural Street Management Committee and the Tiangong Palace of Nankai District of Tianjin City launched the restoration project of the Temple of Tin Hau and the murals in the Temple.
The restoration project was led by Cai Changkui and invited four famous national painters to participate.
The restoration work is based on the principle of "repairing as old as old", and at the same time, the original murals have been adjusted to adjust the local content, and the original imperfect place of the murals has been supplemented and restored.
In the process of repair, we have also made innovations and attempts in color, materials, pen and ink.
After the restoration, the style, spirituality, spirit and artistic style of the original murals were maintained.
The Tin Hau Palace was built in 1326, formerly known as the Tianfei Palace, commonly known as the Mother's Palace, after many renovations, is the oldest building complex in Tianjin, and is also one of the earliest existing Mazu Temple in China.
On September 25, the inauguration ceremony of Beijing Daxing International Airport was held.
The shape of the terminal of Beijing Daxing International Airport means "phoenix wings", and is known as the first of the "seven wonders of the new world".
At present, Beijing Capital International Airport is already overloaded, carrying 100 million passengers last year, becoming the second airport in the world with more than 100 million passengers in the past year after Atlanta Airport in the United States.
It is expected that by 2022, the passenger throughput of Beijing Daxing International Airport will reach 45 million passengers, accounting for 20% of international flights; by 2025, the passenger throughput will reach 72 million passengers, and the proportion of international flights is expected to reach 30%.
As a "new country", how cool is it?
Beijing Daxing International Airport is located between Beijing Daxing District and Guangyang District of Langfang City, Hebei Province, and is 46 kilometers away from Tiananmen Square, which is currently the largest new airport under construction in the world.
The ground projection area of the roof cover steel structure of its terminal terminal reaches 180,000 square meters, and the size of 25 standard football fields.
Beijing Daxing International Airport is the world's first terminal with two arrivals and two departures - F1-F4 is international arrival, domestic arrival, domestic departure, international departure.
The double-dear bridge connecting the high-speed and the airport outside the terminal corresponds to the F3 and F4 terminals, respectively, and the international departures are on the upper floor, and the domestic departures can be on both floors.
The first flight of Beijing Daxing International Airport opened the era of Beijing's "double airport".
The new airport is positioned as a large international aviation hub, the country's development of a new power source, support the construction of Xiong'an New Area of the Beijing-Tianjin-Hebei regional comprehensive transport hub, as of now, a total of 66 airlines intend to enter Beijing Daxing International Airport, of which 20 domestic airlines, 46 Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan regional and foreign airlines, the airline flight time has been approved.
In the winter and spring of 2019, Beijing Daxing International Airport is expected to open 116 routes, including 101 domestic routes and 15 international routes; covering 112 destinations around the world, including 97 domestic destinations and 15 international destinations.
This is the "double hub" airport pattern that forms a coordinated development, moderate competition and international first-class competitiveness with Beijing Capital International Airport, which not only alleviates the operating pressure of the saturated capacity of the capital airport, but also better meets the urgent need for the rapid growth of air transportation in Beijing and surrounding areas, and effectively enhances the international competitiveness of China's civil aviation industry.
In order to ensure efficiency and quality, Beijing Daxing International Airport fully considers the relationship between geographical location, airport and surrounding airspace and operating environment, the airport runway in the country for the first time to adopt a "full-way" layout, the use of the world's largest air traffic control automation system, the establishment of China's largest terminal control area, can maximize the efficiency of aviation operation.
For the first time, domestic airports of this scale have used a localized baggage automatic processing and information management system, using an innovative baggage transmission mode to improve the handling efficiency of the baggage system.
The first flight of Beijing Daxing International Airport indicates that the Phoenix has its wings and cool take off.
This has created more than 40 international and domestic first, and the localization rate has reached more than 98% of the new airport, which will have a direct and indirect economic impact on the industries in the surrounding areas and inject energy into Beijing's economic development.
MCA tentatively held a general meeting in November to reduce the age of party to 16 years old
MCA tentatively held a central congress in early November to revise the party constitution to the age of joining the party to 16 years old.
As the National Assembly lowered the voting age for the general election, MCA announced that it would hold the 66th Central Congress this year, and proposed to amend the party constitution, including lowering the age of MCA membership from the existing 18 to 16 years old.
MCA President Datuk Seri Wei Jiaxiang said that the Central Committee of the Central Committee of the MCA was originally scheduled to hold the Central Congress on November 2 and 3 this year, but due to the by-election of the parliamentary seat of Tanjung Piai, the date of the congress may change.
He said that since the Election Commission would meet on October 1 to finalize the nomination day for the by-election of the Tanjung Biai seat and the voting day, they would meet on the following day, October 2, to discuss whether to change the date of this year's Central Congress.
He also explained that the purpose of the Chinese Central Committee held yesterday (26th) is to finalize the date of the congress and amend the party constitution, but just happened to meet the indigenous unity party Tanjung Piai MP Datuk Mohd Fare, who died unfortunately, so he joined the agenda of the national seat by-election.
