On September 26, local time, State Councilor and Foreign Minister Wang Yi presided over the meeting of foreign ministers of China and the African members of the Security Council at the United Nations Headquarters in New York.
The current African Security Council members of Côte d'Ivoire Foreign Minister Tano, Equatorial Guinea Foreign Minister Oyono, South African Foreign Minister Pandor and the member Niger, Minister of Foreign Affairs of Niger, and Tunisian Foreign Minister Jeshinawi attended the meeting.
Wang Yi put forward four suggestions on strengthening cooperation between China and Africa in the Security Council.
First, by strength.
The biggest challenge in the current international situation is unilateralism, and the immediate consequence is that the basic norms of international relations are challenged, and the role of the United Nations is affected, which harms the interests of developing countries and small and medium-sized countries, including African countries.
To deal with this challenge, China and Africa need to hold hands, shoulder to shoulder, and unity to have strength.
In the Security Council, the three African countries speak with one voice, focusing on the weight is not just three votes, but the entire African continent.
China and Africa stand together not only with four votes, but will lead other countries to follow up, influence and shape the agenda of the Security Council.
Since 2018, China and African members of the Security Council have established a "3+1" coordination mechanism, and this coordination mechanism should be fully utilized.
Second, the dispute is settled through consultation.
China has always advocated the political settlement of hotspot issues, and Africa has a good tradition of consultation and the experience of successful mediation by African regional and subregional organizations.
Many of the complex challenges on the Council's agenda, especially in Africa, are mostly the banes of colonialism, some directly related to external factors.
We must make good use of Chapter VI of the Charter of the United Nations and play a good role in the good offices and mediation of the United Nations.
Third, rely on self-reliance.
African countries and people know the problems of Africa best, and Africa has the ability and wisdom to solve its own problems.
When the Council addresses the hot issues in Africa, it should focus on listening and respecting Africa's will, should play the role of regional and subregional organizations, and should encourage and support endogenous solutions from Africa.
China is willing to strengthen coordination with Africa and firmly promote the capacity-building of independent peace operations in Africa.
Fourth, it is based on development.
China and the vast majority of African countries are developing countries, and we must adhere to putting economic and social development first and support each other's choice of development path.
China is willing to work together to build the Belt and Road Initiative with the African Union's Agenda 2063, the United Nations 2030 Agenda for Sustainable Development, and the development strategies of African countries to help African countries enhance their development capabilities and eliminate the root causes of conflict.
We must jointly promote the United Nations to increase investment in Africa's development.
With the outbreak of the Ebola epidemic in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) again, China has made every effort and will continue to do its best to provide human and material assistance within its capacity, and is willing to coordinate actions with African countries to mobilize the United Nations, WHO and other countries to increase assistance and play the role of the United Nations Stabilization Mission in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC).
The neonatal department and other relays have saved small lives.
The thrill!
The second-born mother had an early attack, and on the way to the hospital in a hurry, a 32-week premature baby could not wait to be born in her father's car.
Fortunately, obstetrics and neonatologists handled it in time, and the relay saved this small life.
Coincidentally, on the 19th, 20th and 21st, the obstetrics and neonatology department of Hubei Provincial Maternal and Child Health Hospital received three premature babies born on the road for three consecutive days, and the other two were born in 120 emergency vehicles, all of which were premature babies of 29 weeks.
Ms. Cheng is a second-born mother, September 19th at 7 a.m., she felt a little pain in her stomach, thinking that she was 32 weeks pregnant, and the first child was premature, she packed up the items to be given, ready to take a bath and go straight to the hospital.
After 9:30, Ms. Cheng packed up and let her husband drive from Xudong's home to the hospital.
I did not expect that the car had just opened out of the house soon, the baby could not wait to be born in the father's car co-driver.
20 minutes later, Ms. Cheng and the baby finally arrived at the Obstetrics and Gynecology Building of Hubei Maternal and Child Health Hospital.
The hospital security saw the panicked husband and wife and the baby, immediately notified the obstetric delivery room, deputy doctor Zhang Huan and other four doctors and midwife Liu Yanyan with the delivery bag and umbilical cord rushed downstairs.
"At that time, the mother half lying on the car co-driver, under the amniotic fluid and blood water, a baby boy is next to, but also connected with the umbilical cord."
Zhang Huan asked to know that the baby is a 32-week premature baby, the parents on the way did not have time to cover the package for the child, the early autumn morning has a cool, he colded his skin pale, no crying, paralysis of the limbs.
Liu Yanyan rushed to the co-pilot to deal with the baby umbilical cord, Zhang Huan drilled in from the cab, quickly opened the production bag, with the treatment towel and bag of the bag to the child to cover a few layers of warmth, and to the newborn to clean the respiratory tract (pictured), and then hold the baby to the 12th floor of the neonatal department.
After the neontology medical care learned the news, he immediately rushed to the nurse station to rescue the premature baby.
At that time, the baby's face was purple, there was suffocation and lack of oxygen, the doctor immediately gave him a trachea intubation, less than a minute, the baby regained its heartbeat, the skin color gradually returned to rosy, recovery success.
After being admitted to the hospital, the 32-week-old baby was on a ventilator, and after continuous rescue, his breathing was stable, and he had successfully withdrawn the next day.
After a week of treatment, the baby's vital signs are stable and breathing is smooth, and a small amount of breastfeeding has begun.
Coincidentally, on the 19th, 20th and 21st, the obstetrics and neonatology department of the hospital received three premature babies born on the road for three consecutive days, and the other two were born in 120 emergency vehicles, all of which were preterm babies of 29 weeks, and are currently actively treated in the neonatal department.
Sun Guoqiang, director of the obstetrics department of the Provincial Maternal and Child Health Hospital, said that in recent years, the provincial mother and child have received a lot of babies born in subways and private cars, which may threaten the life safety of mother and child.
Director Sun reminded that once the pregnant mother has abdominal pain, broken water, red and other phenomena, she should immediately come to the hospital for treatment.
If you are at home or on the road, the mother should be as flat as possible, you can put a blanket on the hips, etc., to prevent the baby from hitting the ground after delivery, the child should be warm immediately after delivery, as soon as possible to send a doctor.
Vietnam-Singapore Aviation Technology Company Officially Opens
The establishment of VSTEA is one of the details of the memorandum of understanding signed by VAECO and ST Engineering Aerospace in April 2018, marking the introduction of the first aircraft equipment maintenance and repair joint venture in Vietnam.
Two leading aviation technology companies from Vietnam and Singapore have cooperated to provide aircraft equipment maintenance and repair services to domestic and foreign airlines.
