During the year, the repurchase scale of listed companies exceeded 100 billion yuan, a record high - Xinhua
In order to stabilize the company's stock price and maintain the company's image, listed companies have begun to repurchase shares frequently in the past two years, and hope to pass the information on the undervaluation of the company to the market through targeted repurchases and collective bidding transactions, so as to stabilize the stock price and enhance investor confidence.
Oriental Wealth Choice data show that in 2017, the funds used by listed companies to repurchase shares were 7.9 billion yuan, which soared to 51 billion yuan in 2018, and since 2019, the total amount of repurchase implementation of A-share listed companies has exceeded 100 billion yuan, setting a new high in the amount of A-share repurchase funds, and far exceeding the previous year.
From the perspective of the purpose of repurchase, the company's repurchase of shares seems to be the same as the increase in the shareholding of major shareholders, but there are great differences in the implementation of the main body, the source of funds, the use of repurchase, and the equity of the stock itself.
Xu Yang, chairman of Shanghai Mei Kerong Information Consulting Co., Ltd., said in an interview with the "Securities Daily" reporter that in November 2018, the "Opinions on Supporting Listed Companies to Repurchase Shares" was revised in response to the existing system such as narrow share repurchase range, complex decision-making procedures, and incomplete inventory system.
In January this year, the Shanghai Stock Exchange and the Shenzhen Stock Exchange officially released the "Implementation Rules for Repurchase Shares by Listed Companies", which broadened the source of repurchase funds for listed companies, appropriately simplified implementation procedures, guided and improved governance arrangements, and encouraged all kinds of listed companies to implement equity incentives or employee stock ownership plans.
After the introduction of the opinion, the operation of the share repurchase by the listed company has more applicable circumstances, the repurchase process is simpler, and the enthusiasm for share repurchase is greater.
Repurchasing shares in a relatively low position is also conducive to listed companies to improve the efficiency of the use of funds, thereby increasing the level of profit per share, increasing the return on net assets, and reducing the pressure on the company's profit indicators.
Compared with the increase in the holdings of major shareholders, the significance of repurchased shares by listed companies is greater, which also reflects the willingness of listed companies to manage their active market value and cash flow.
Xu Yang believes that the undervaluation of the stock price is the main factor of the repurchase of listed companies, the company's stock price has not been able to reflect the future development prospects of the company, so such companies are worthy of investors' attention, but can not blindly invest, need to pay attention to the financial reports of such listed companies and the specific operation.
Listed companies with large-scale repurchase behavior at least show the company's development confidence and financial strength.
The enthusiasm for repurchases of A-share listed companies has gradually warmed up, and the repurchase behavior has also been normalized, and the data shows that nearly 1,000 listed companies have implemented share repurchases this year, and the leading companies in various industries have become the main force in the repurchase market.
China Ping An recently disclosed the progress of repurchases, saying that the company has repurchased 57.59 million shares of A shares through centralized bidding transactions, accounting for 0.315% of the total share capital of the company, and the total amount of funds paid is 5 billion yuan (excluding transaction fees), and the repurchased shares will all be used for employee stock ownership plans, including but not limited to the long-term service plan that the company's shareholders' meeting has considered and adopted.
Yili shares have paid 5.792 billion yuan for share repurchase, and in the near future to adjust the use of repurchase shares, the original plan "repurchase shares will be used as a source of late-stage implementation of equity incentives of the stock" to "accumulative repurchase of 183 million shares, of which 152 million shares for the implementation of equity incentives of the stock source, the remaining 30.49 million shares will be used to cancel to reduce registered capital."
Yili said that the cancellation of some of the shares that have been repurchased is conducive to further improving the level of earnings per share and effectively improving the return on investment of the company's shareholders.
TCL Group released a repurchase progress announcement on September 25, showing that TCL Group has repurchased 3.59% of the company's shares, at a total cost of 1.65 billion yuan.
The office of the board of directors of TCL Group told the Securities Daily reporter that the repurchased shares will be used for employee stock ownership plans, equity incentives or corporate bonds that can be converted into stocks issued by listed companies.
TCL Group adheres to the established business strategy, continuously improves competitiveness and sustains healthy development.
Based on the confidence in the future development of the company and the maintenance of investors' interests, combined with the performance of the company's stock in the secondary market in the past year, and taking into account the company's operating conditions and financial situation, the company plans to use its own funds, self-financing and other financing methods to buy back the company's shares.
