Gansu Qingyang: Lake sheep to "poverty alleviation".
The autumn of September renders the Loess Plateau.
In the Yimin breeding professional cooperative in Yima Town, Chavili, a 58-year-old villager, filled the trough in the sheep pen with the last shovel grass, guarded by the trough, and watched the white lake sheep chewing.
"Eat well, wait until autumn and winter is full, out of the market to sell a good price."
Shavili said that he feeds sheep a "special nutritious meal" every day, regularly cleans and disinfects, and carelessly does not dare to slack off.
Shavili raised sheep for more than 20 years, until he came to the cooperative to work, he knew how extensive sheep was in the past.
Shavili is a native of Xiayuchi Village, Qingcheng County, Qingyang City, Gansu Province.
His left neighbor and right are sheep farmers, but adhere to the traditional free-range mode, the quality of the sheep is poor, and the amount of the market is small.
In June this year, under the guidance of the government, 140 poor people in the village joined the cooperative, and everything began to change.
Shavilli buried his head all day to study farming, because he always held a breath in his heart.
The people who invested in the shares are all poor households, and they all trust the sheep to the cooperative, and whether they can pay dividends and sell the price at the end of the year can count on him.
Fortunately, under the guidance of technicians, he slowly learned to engage in epidemic prevention, mastered scientific feeding, and became one of the few breeding "good style" in the village.
Yimin breeding professional cooperative is a standardized cooperative, a total of 16 sheep sheds, breeding nearly 1,400 lake sheep.
Zou Tao, the head of the cooperative, said that there are many doorways inside and outside the standardized sheep shed.
"The wool is thick, easy to breed bacteria, the lake sheep in the sweltering and wet place to stay, the sheep shed must be built in the three sides of the ditch, but also have to install a change of fan to ventilate and dissipate heat."
Zou Tao said that in order to prevent the epidemic, it is also necessary to regularly disinfect the sheep shed spray, and give the sheep three to four epidemic prevention injections in the first quarter.
In addition to living well, the "little fat sheep" also have to eat grass mixed with silage corn, wheatgrass, alfalfa, etc., and have a wide enough " playground" to stretch the bones.
The cooperative adopts the method of trusteeship and maintenance, guides local farmers to put good-growing lake sheep here, unified breeding, management and sales, and realizes good seeding, scientificization, standardization, and intensive breeding.
Today, 140 poor households with sheep shareholds have a dividend of more than 6,000 yuan per household per year, and 4 poverty alleviation targets are working in cooperatives.
From "full mountain grazing" to "accurate feeding", from "local mating" to "artificial insemination", from "looking at the body type, touching the belly" to "doing B super"... In Qingyang, Gansu, sheep farming is not only a change in the way of feeding, "leading enterprises + cooperatives + farmers" model is to change the scene of "raising sheep on the hillside, selling sheep in the market", overcoming the weakness of traditional agriculture and animal husbandry.
Zou Tao said that if the market price is weak, the local leading enterprise Gansu Zhongsheng Agricultural and Animal Husbandry Development Co., Ltd. will be acquired with a market protection price of 27 yuan per kilogram to help farmers disperse market risk.
Xu Jianfeng, general adviser of Gansu Zhongsheng Agricultural and Animal Husbandry Development Co., Ltd., said that enterprises have driven more and more poor households to read "sheep" by providing loan guarantees, sheep supply, order farming, quotation acquisition, unified processing and sales services for poor households.
In Qingyang, at least 8,200 poor families have achieved stable income through forage breeding, good seed breeding, large-scale breeding, slaughtering and segmentation, and market sales through "joining" the forage breeding, breeding, large-scale breeding, slaughtering and segmentation, and market sales.
Qingyang City is located in the northern agricultural and animal husbandry staggered belt, and the forage resources are rich.
At present, there are 913 large-scale farms and cooperatives in the city, with more than 5 million sheep breeding, and two processing production lines of 1.3 million sheep slaughtered, and the flock is becoming the "leader" of poverty alleviation in the local industry.
French finance minister says more than 10 billion euros cut next year, calls on Germany to follow
PARIS, Sept 26 (Reuters) - France will cut taxes by more than 10 billion euros ($10.9 billion) next year, French Finance Minister Bruno Le Maire said on Thursday, while Germany should keep pace with France's fiscal stimulus to revive a sluggish economy.
Speaking on France’s 2020 budget, Le Maire said the ECB’s latest monetary easing initiative has created an opportunity to increase investment for those governments of member countries with the ability to afford it.
The European Central Bank cut interest rates to a record low on September 12 and plans to restart bond purchases to drive down borrowing costs, hoping to stimulate economic recovery and push up inflation.
“Low interest rates will not allow Europe to boom again, and monetary policy measures are necessary but not enough,” Le Maire told reporters.
"Germany needs to invest, it needs it now, the sooner the better. Don't wait until the situation gets worse before it takes action," he added.
He has made repeated appeals to Germany.
France has already implemented tax cuts of more than 10 billion euros this year, which has brought a big boost to France's economic growth.
The global economy has lost momentum, and the German economy, which relies on exports, has borne the brunt.
Le Maire pointed out that the tax burden on French families will be reduced by 9.3 billion euros next year, including a 5 billion euro income tax relief.
In addition, with the gradual implementation of the corporate tax rate will be reduced from 33.3% to 25% over a five-year period, the corporate tax burden will be reduced by nearly 1 billion euros.
