The deepest record of China's railway tunnel shaft has been set
China New Social Security Mountain September 27th (Zhang Weiming Xuweizhou Jingbo) after more than 1200 days of day and night construction, in the construction of Da (Li) Rui (Li) railway Gaoligongshan Tunnel No. 1 shaft completed excavation on the 27th, the well depth reached 762.59 meters below the ground, breaking the Chinese railway tunnel shaft record, and this record is created in a large amount of water.
The 34.5-kilometer-long Da Rui Railway Gaoligong Mountain Tunnel is located in Yunnan, and the tunnel crosses the Gaoligong Mountain Mountains on the west bank of the Fur River, making it the longest tunnel in Asia.
The tunnel passes through 19 fracture zones with a maximum depth of 1,155 meters, as it covers almost all the bad geology and major risks that may be encountered in tunnel construction, and the Gaoligong Mountain Tunnel is known as the "geological museum" of tunnel construction.
The shaft is the most important auxiliary pit lane of the Gaoligongshan Tunnel, and it is an important task to increase the operation surface to achieve "long tunnel short fight" and the ventilation of railway operation in the later period.
The successful excavation of the No. 1 shaft to the bottom of the well marks the official entry of the Gaoligong Mountain Tunnel into the horizontal tunnel construction, and after the excavation and equipment replacement of the well bottom yard, the underground can add 4 operating surfaces to speed up the excavation speed of the tunnel.
"The shaft is all in the granite formation, because the granite slattice cracks are more, can not stop the water, from top to bottom non-stop, basically how deep the well has how much deep water pressure is how big."
Shi Jingzhao, chief engineer of the Da Rui Railway Project Department of the China Railway Tunnel Bureau, told reporters that in the construction of the shaft, there have been many dangerous situations such as sudden mud and water, collapse, etc. The construction party invited experts to put the pulse on the spot and discuss the treatment plan more than 20 times.
"When the maximum water in the shaft is up to 300 cubic meters per hour, the bottom of the well with a depth of more than 700 meters, the water pressure is equivalent to 700 meters deep at the bottom of the sea."
"If you don't drain in time, you'll flood the well 10 meters in an hour, we're going to spend almost 85% of our time on water and 15% of our time digging."
In order to overcome the geological problems such as longitudinal development, sudden mud surge water, and water-rich granite, tunnel construction adopts systematic water treatment measures combined with "exploration, injection and excavation" to reduce construction risks.
After many improvements, the construction of the No. 1 shaft has formed a mechanized assembly line such as excavation system, lifting system, suspension system, and winch lifting system, which has realized the full process mechanization operation of eye-booling, blasting, billing, template installation, concrete pouring, and accelerated the construction progress.
Finally, after more than 1,200 days of day and night construction, the shaft successfully completed the excavation of 762.59 meters.
With a total length of 330 kilometers, the Darui Railway is an important part of the China-Myanmar international channel and an important transportation infrastructure for the implementation of the “Belt and Road” construction.
After the completion of the opening of the car, Dali to Ruili's driving time will be shortened from the current six hours of the road to 2 hours, which will greatly improve the transportation pattern in the Dianxi region and promote economic and trade cooperation and personnel-friendly exchanges between China and South Asian countries.
