British tourist car key dropped into the lake, the whole family was trapped in France for five days
Recently, a couple in Wales, England, took two children to France for a holiday, and accidentally dropped the car key into the lake, and the whole family was forced to wait five days to get the new keys formulated by the car manufacturer.
The couple then left France with the children.
According to reports, on September 16, local time, when the British family visited a lake in France, her daughter accidentally knocked over a leather bag and the car keys inside fell into the lake.
But it took a few hours and they couldn’t find the key.
All their belongings and cash are locked in the car.
Despite the fact that British tourists bought insurance before departure, insurance companies refused to help on the grounds that the vehicle was not in danger of being stolen.
They hired a trailer to pull the car to a repair shop and re-order the keys from the car manufacturer.
A few days later, British tourists finally got the keys that were formulated, and the couple left France with their children.
Their planned journey was cancelled due to the loss of the car key.
