Pilot notification commitment system in the field of low-risk food production license, and decentralization of foreign business representative offices to the free trade zone
On the 27th, the Shanghai Municipal Market Supervision Bureau and the Pudong New Area Government signed a working memorandum and launched 20 market supervision reform measures, some of which are the first pilots in the country.
According to reports, the notification commitment refers to the administrative organ in the relevant licensing registration matters, in writing the conditions and requirements stipulated in the laws and regulations to inform the applicant a one-time.
After the applicant signs the commitment, the administrative organ can handle it directly.
According to the memorandum, the Shanghai market supervision department will support the Pudong New Area and the Shanghai Pilot Free Trade Zone to register the enterprise name, handle the production license of simple process, low-risk varieties of food, and the three-area pilot notification commitment system such as the approval of some measuring instruments, so that the access of enterprises is more convenient.
Shanghai Shao Wansheng Food Co., Ltd. 27 through the way of notification of the commitment to obtain the "food production license" on the spot, become the first to enjoy the pilot dividend of the enterprise.
The person in charge of the enterprise said that the food license can also be certified on the spot, and also adopted the "receive" approach, that is, allow the enterprise to submit some materials in accordance with the deadline agreed upon in the notification of the commitment, "really feel the convenience of reform."
Shanghai market regulators said that the implementation of the notification commitment system for food production licenses is the first pilot in the country.
After the reform, the approval process was compressed from the previous six links of "registration, acceptance, on-site verification, sample inspection, material review, approval and certification" to "registration, acceptance, approval and certification", and the completion time was shortened from 20 working days before the reform to on-site.
Taking into account the high degree of export-to-export of Pudong, the Shanghai market supervision department has delegated the registration authority of the permanent representative offices of foreign (regional) enterprises to the Shanghai Free Trade Zone to facilitate the nearby processing of enterprises.
Statistics show that the decentralization involves a total of 1,592 permanent representative offices in the Shanghai Free Trade Zone, of which 99 have been handled in accordance with the new regulations.
