Starting next year, Chinese students can apply for German undergraduates with college entrance examination results.
Recently, Germany is responsible for the evaluation and certification of foreign academic qualifications Anabin database announced on the official website: 2020, China's high school graduates can apply directly to the German university with the college entrance examination results, do not need to first enroll in the domestic university enrollment.
Prior to this, Chinese high school graduates who wanted to apply to a German university needed to study for one semester (211,985 universities) or three semesters (general undergraduates) in China, and passed the APS audit or TestAS exam.
The release of the new regulations may save at least half a year for Chinese students who are willing to study in Germany.
It is reported that the new regulations will come into effect in the second half of 2019.
Applicants need to: complete 12 years of regular compulsory education, obtain a high school diploma; participate in the college entrance examination, college entrance examination, and college entrance examination score of 70% or more (if the total score of 750 points, you need to reach more than 525 points), and including two language scores and one mathematics or natural science performance requirements.
In addition, the requirements of specific professions for college entrance examination results are not the same.
For example, applying for medical science, dental medicine, veterinary medicine, pharmacy and other majors, college entrance examination scores must reach a full score of 80%, and college entrance examination subjects must include mathematics, physics, chemistry, biology in at least two, or participate in the integration; apply for legal majors, college entrance examination scores need to reach a full score of 80%, and college entrance examination subjects must contain foreign languages, history, geography at least two, or participate in the synthesis.
According to incomplete statistics, many countries, including Germany, the United Kingdom, Canada, Australia and other countries, have recognized the results of the Chinese college entrance examination.
Taking the United Kingdom as an example, universities such as the University of Cambridge, the University of Birmingham and the University of Leicester have accepted Chinese students to apply for study with college entrance examination results.
