A villager in Baokang County, Hubei Province, was ordered to hunt wild animals.
A villager in Baokang County, Hubei Province, was sentenced for hunting wild animals and ordered to compensate for the cost of ecological resource environmental damage repair of 15,420 yuan (RMB, the same below).
Due to the poverty of the defendant's family, the procuratorial organs used alternative labor to compensate for the cost of ecological restoration, and realized the organic unity of legal and social effects.
Wang Zhongliang, deputy procurator general of Baokang County Procuratorate, introduced on the 27th that through three months of alternative labor such as "commitment to patrol the mountain", the defendant Zhou has established deep feelings with wild macaque monkeys, and deeply blames himself for the previous animal hunting behavior.
On June 21 this year, a criminal incidental civil public interest lawsuit in the field of ecological resources filed by the Baokang County Procuratorate was heard in public and pronounced in court in the county court.
The defendant Zhou was sentenced to 3 years in prison, suspended for 4 years, and fined 3,000 yuan, while ordering him to compensate for the cost of ecological resource environmental damage repair of 15,420 yuan.
After investigation, Zhou began to set up a power grid at the cliffs in late January 2014, and has hunted more than 20 wild animals, including antelopes, small lanterns, and hairy crown deer.
The antelope belongs to the national second-class endangered wild protection animals, and the small lut and the hairy deer are listed in the National Terrestrial Wildlife Protection List.
During the trial, Zhou confessed to his illegal facts and behavior, and was willing to bear incidental civil liability.
However, considering the poor economic situation of Zhou's family, under the coordination of the Baokang County Procuratorate, the local village committee, forest station and Zhou reached an agreement on alternative labor compensation for ecological restoration costs: that is, Zhou Mou provided public welfare services to offset the ecological restoration costs by carrying out macaque macaques care work in the village macaque protection area, compulsory mountain patrol, and forest protection for one year.
For the prosecutor's proposal, the court expressed its approval, agreeing to Zhou's execution of the suspended sentence while actively fulfilling the obligation of "alternative labor to compensate for ecological restoration costs".
At present, Zhou has been working in the macaque reserve for 3 months, and the mountain is active and performs well.
In recent years, the Baokang County Procuratorate has organically integrated procuratorial functions and social governance behavior in practice, and scientifically used supervision methods such as procuratorial recommendations, investigation supervision, and litigation supervision to minimize the damage caused by criminal acts to the ecological environment through judicial means.
