Economic and trade frictions affect the "report card" of the US economy.
The U.S. economic "report card" in the second quarter of this year showed that the growth rate of U.S. gross domestic product (GDP) slowed significantly from the previous quarter due to a sharp decline in private-sector investment and exports.
Analysts pointed out that economic and trade frictions and the uncertainty they brought about were the main reasons for the decline in private sector investment and exports in the second quarter.
The final revised data released by the US Department of Commerce on the 26th showed that the US GDP grew by 2% year-on-year in the second quarter, which was the same as the previously released revised data, but significantly lower than the 3.1% in the first quarter.
The data shows that consumption growth has become a major factor supporting the economic growth of the United States in the second quarter.
Personal consumption expenditure, which accounts for about 70% of the total U.S. economy, increased by 4.6% quarter-on-quarter, driving economic growth by 3.03 percentage points.
In addition, government consumption expenditure and investment drove economic growth by 0.82 percentage points.
However, private sector investment in the second quarter fell 6.3% from the previous quarter, dragging down the quarter's economic growth by 1.16 percentage points; exports fell 5.7% from the previous quarter, and net exports dragged down the quarter's economic growth by 0.68 percentage points.
Barry Knapp, managing partner of Ainside Macroeconomics Consulting in the United States, said that private sector investment not only failed to maintain the momentum of last year's growth, but also fell sharply, because economic and trade frictions and rising uncertainty hit business confidence.
Knapp believes that under the influence of policy uncertainty, US corporate capital expenditure is expected to remain in a downward trend next year.
Analysts believe that although consumption growth has formed a strong support for the US economy in the second quarter, there are increasing signs that economic and trade frictions and the uncertainty they bring have affected consumer confidence and adversely affect the US consumption prospects.
Richard Curtin, a professor of economics at the University of Michigan and the head of the survey, said that in the latest survey, 38% of consumers spontaneously mentioned the negative impact of tariffs on the US economy, which is the highest in a year and a half.
For the future trend of the US economy, analysts generally believe that the US economy will continue to slow down.
However, some experts said that if the economic and trade frictions were eased, the performance of the US industrial sector and financial markets would improve.
Kathleen Birch, a global economist at the Economist Intelligence Unit, expects that in the future, the US economy will continue the gradual downward trend since this year, and the growth rate will fall to a lower level than in the second quarter.
Mark Zandi, chief economist at Moody's Analytics, predicts that the U.S. economy will grow at a rate of 2.3% this year and 1.6% next year, assuming that economic and trade frictions will not continue to escalate.
Ellen Hazen, investment manager of Patnam Investment Company, pointed out that the biggest concern of enterprises at present is the economic and trade disputes and the uncertainties they bring, if the economic and trade disputes can be resolved, the uncertainty will be greatly reduced, and the performance of the industrial sector will be much better than now.
Miller-Thaback Asset Management stock strategist Matt Meley said that economic and trade frictions are still the "primary problem", but also the main reason for the sharp fluctuations in the US capital market this year, whether economic and trade frictions can be properly resolved, will be the key to affecting the direction of the US capital market for the rest of this year.
Parents of children 0 to 3 years old can take 10 days off per year in Ningxia
Protecting the legitimate rights and interests of women is a manifestation of respecting and protecting human rights, and it is also an important symbol of the progress of social civilization.
On September 27, at the 15th meeting of the Standing Committee of the 12th National People's Congress of Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region, the "Regulations on the Protection of Women's Rights and Interests in Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region" was passed with a high ticket.
This is the first provincial-level local regulations formulated and promulgated by Ningxia Province to comprehensively and systematically safeguard the legitimate rights and interests of women, which will be formally implemented from November 1, 2019.
It is understood that the "Regulations" adopted this time were revised on the basis of the "Ningxia Implementation of the "People's Rights and Interests Protection Law of the People's Republic of China" in 2007, divided into 9 chapters and 65 articles, including general principles, political rights, cultural and educational rights and interests, labor and social security rights and interests, property rights and interests, personal rights, marriage and family rights, legal responsibilities, and by-laws.
In the Regulations, Ningxia encouraged the exploration of the implementation of joint parental leave for husband and wife, which is still the first in the country.
In April this year, the "Guiding Opinions on Promoting the Development of Care Services for Infants and Young Children Under 3 Years of Age" promulgated by the General Office of the State Council has a relevant description of the common parenting of husband and wife.
In the process of revising the Regulations, Ningxia innovatively proposed to "encourage employers to give each of them 10 days of joint parental leave each year between the children of children and couples who have children in accordance with the provisions of the law and regulations."
At the same time, the Ordinance highlights the protection against sexual harassment and the protection of female minors.
Article 43 of the Regulations incorporates the latest legislative achievements in the current human rights of the Civil Code of China, and refines the elements of sexual harassment, the subject and mechanism of anti-sexual harassment.
Article 44 of the Ordinance prohibits frequent sexual assault of girls, and requires educational institutions to carry out relevant education, protection and prevention work, which has become a new benchmark for the protection of girls in local legislation.
In response to women's right to information and treatment of common property in marriage and family, Article 35 of the Regulations clearly stipulates that women's right to know and the obligations of property registration agencies and related subjects on common property clearly stipulate that women's rights to protect their rights provide solid institutional support for women's rights.
