Is the exercise tired and tired?
According to the Russian satellite network, a study of athletes shows that after high-intensity exercise, the brain will also show signs of fatigue.
The study, led by Mathias Pessigrion, an expert at the Pittier-Salpetril hospital in France, shows that there is no obvious link between mental and physical labor: both require cognitive control of activity.
“You need to control the autonomous process that forces yourself to stop when your muscles and joints are in pain,” Pesigrion explains.
The study was initiated by the French National Institute of Sport (INSEP).
The school’s experts are responsible for guiding athletes in preparing for the Olympics.
Some athletes have begun to suffer from overtraining syndrome, that is, there is an irrepressible feeling of fatigue after high-load exercise, the body can not recover, and the performance has declined.
INSEP asks the question: Will part of the cause of this condition be nerve fatigue, the kind of nerve fatigue caused by excessive mental labor?
The study was published in the journal Current Biology.
