Fujian Provincial Tax Bank Convenient Comprehensive Tax Payment Platform was officially launched.
Zhongxin Net Fuzhou September 27th (Yeqiuyun) Fujian Provincial Tax Bank convenient comprehensive tax payment platform on September 27th in Fuzhou City, Fujian Province officially launched.
The reporter learned that on October 26, 2018, the Fujian Provincial Taxation Bureau of the Fuzhou Central Branch of the People's Bank of China and China UnionPay Co., Ltd. jointly signed a memorandum of understanding on tripartite cooperation, creating a comprehensive tax payment platform for the convenience of the Fujian Provincial Tax Bank in the country.
After nearly a year of construction, the platform has been successfully launched.
Wang Dehui, director of the treasury department of the Fuzhou Central Branch of the People's Bank of China, introduced that the platform adheres to the construction concept of security, versatility, convenience, compliance and leadingness, and connects tax, government, bank, non-bank payment institutions and social service providers at the front end, providing mobile APP, WeChat public number, tax hall, bank branch, inclusive financial service points and other online and offline tax payment channels, and connecting the state treasury and tax system.
It is reported that the platform brings together a number of Huimin convenience projects, of which urban and rural residents' medical insurance fee collection projects have been officially launched.
The project has opened 14 online and offline channels, which can provide services to more than 30 million urban and rural residents in Fujian Province, covering 76% of the resident population of Fujian Province.
Online can pay medical insurance fees through "Min Tax Pass", "Cloud Flash Pay" and the APP of various banks, WeChat public number; offline can be sent to Fujian Province's tax halls and rural inclusive financial service points to use scan code, wave card, swipe card and other ways to pay medical insurance fees.
Shi Dong, deputy governor of the Fuzhou Central Branch of the People's Bank of China, said that the successful launch of the platform, while ensuring the direct payment of government revenue to the warehouse and real-time interaction of data information, can provide a safe, efficient, multi-channel, multi-mode convenience tax payment service for the public.
At present, more than 16,000 inclusive financial service points in the province, more than 9,000 have opened the medical insurance fee investigation and payment function, to achieve rural residents "out of the village" can be at ease to check and pay medical insurance premiums, so that the public has a stronger sense of "gains", "happiness".
According to statistics, since the early trial operation of the platform's urban and rural residents' medical insurance fees, the service users have reached 840,000, of which 750,000 have been online payment users and nearly 20,000 users of inclusive financial service points.
In addition, Lin Guojie, deputy director of the Fujian Provincial Taxation Bureau of the State Administration of Taxation, revealed at the event that the platform is the first to apply blockchain electronic payment certificate technology in the country.
Starting from the next month, after the payer completes the payment, he can also download the electronic payment certificate with the stamped seal directly through the mobile phone.
Fujian tax information network based on blockchain technology is being built, and the "highway" to facilitate private tax payment will be further broadened.
