Guo Zhi, chief economist of the National Energy Administration, said that the Qiandong to Wannan Project is the world's largest power transmission capacity and the farthest transmission distance.
Its operation is of great significance to promote the development of Xinjiang's energy base and ensure the power supply in East China.
GIL, that is, gas-insulated metal closed transmission lines.
The Sutong pipe gallery project has created the record of the highest global voltage level and strongest conveying capacity of the GIL project, and realized the "AC double ring network" joint operation of the highest voltage level of the backbone power grid in East China.
