The reporter learned from the Yunnan Provincial Academy of Agricultural Sciences on the 27th that at present, the Yunnan grassland nocturnal moth has been effectively prevented and controlled, which has not caused a large-scale outbreak of disaster, and the prevention and control work has achieved phased results.
In January this year, the first time that the grassland moths that moved into the country were found in Jiangcheng County in Pu'er City, Yunnan Province, it was confirmed in 129 counties in Yunnan that the grassland nocturne moth also spread from Yunnan to mainland China, posing a direct threat to Chinese food production.
The grassland nocturnal moth is a multi-eating long-distance migratory agricultural pest native to the tropical and subtropical regions of the Americas, and is a major migratory pest in the global warning of the United Nations Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations, which is characterized by "international, flying, explosive and destructive".
The pest harms more than 80 kinds of crops such as corn, sugar cane, and sorghum, and the intake is large, which can cause up to 70% of the production loss.
The prevention and control is difficult, and there is no registered pesticide for the prevention and control of the worm in China.
Since the grassland nocturnal moths moved into Yunnan, the Yunnan Provincial Academy of Agricultural Sciences selected Chen Aidong researchers to lead the Yunnan Provincial Academy of Agricultural Sciences cross-border pests and collaborative green prevention and control provincial innovation team, to the front line, field investigation, sample collection, and technical guidance and test demonstration.
The team has initially mastered the population characteristics of the nocturnal moth in Yunnan grassland, the resources of natural enemy insects, the characteristics of overseas insect sources, the trajectory of population migration, the virulence of pharmaceuticals and the effect of field prevention and control.
They actively carry out research and application of green prevention and control technology, through the implementation of new technologies such as population monitoring, adult booby-trapping, scientific drugs and agronomic measures, the prevention and control effect in the demonstration area has reached more than 90%, while reducing the use of chemical pesticides, protecting the resources and ecological environment of natural enemies, and providing technical support for Yunnan to effectively control the outbreak of grassland nocturne.
At present, the Yunnan grassland nocturnal moth has been effectively prevented and controlled, and it has not caused a large-scale outbreak of disasters, and the prevention and control work has achieved phased results.
In the next step, the Yunnan Provincial Academy of Agricultural Sciences will focus on the ecological mechanism of population relocation and invasion, and break through the construction of biological prevention and control and green prevention and control technology system.
At the same time, we will actively promote cross-border international cooperation and strive to establish joint key laboratories and joint monitoring outlets and demonstration areas abroad to enhance the comprehensive monitoring and early warning capabilities of Yunnan grassland nocturnal moths.
