The 86th China-Laos Myanmar-Thailand Mekong River joint patrol law enforcement was completed.
The reporter learned from the press office of the Yunnan Provincial Public Security Department on the 27th that at 15:30 on the same day, three Chinese law enforcement boats and two law enforcement boats of Laos participated in the 86th China-Laos-Thailand-Mekong River joint patrol and law enforcement, marking the successful conclusion of the joint patrol law enforcement operation.
The operation was launched in Guanjia Port on the 24th, which lasted 4 days and 3 nights, and the four countries sent a total of 136 law enforcement personnel and 6 law enforcement boats.
During the operation, the formation carried out joint patrols, anti-drug propaganda and other activities in key waters such as the Golden Triangle, Laos Banzhiguo and Monmo.
In addition, China has also sent a team of police actual combat instructors to the 222 and 133 border guards of the Lao People's Army to carry out police combat skills exchanges, effectively improving the emergency response capabilities of law enforcement personnel of the two sides to jointly deal with emergencies.
The four countries also held a law enforcement cooperation exchange meeting in Qingsheng, Thailand, to inform each other about the recent situation of countries in border management, combating drug crimes and the security situation in the Mekong River basin, and reached consensus on strengthening information exchange, research and judgment and law enforcement cooperation, and holding cultural and sports exchange activities in the four countries, carrying out competitions such as football, rattan, iron ball and tug-of-war, effectively enhancing mutual understanding among law enforcement players and the friendship between law enforcement and law enforcement cooperation between the four countries.
According to the relevant person in charge of the water patrol team of the Yunnan Provincial Public Security Department, after the end of the operation, the two sides will continue to carry out a 10-day joint training and segmented joint patrol task to improve the Mekong River police rate and make every effort to maintain the safety and stability of the Mekong River Basin.
The commander of the Thai side said that since the launch of the joint patrol and law enforcement of the Mekong River, the four countries of China and Laos have exchanged close views, deepened practical cooperation, and achieved fruitful results in many fields such as law enforcement and security cooperation and cultural exchanges.
It is hoped that the four-way law enforcement cooperation will continue to deepen and expand, strive to open a new situation of law enforcement cooperation between the four countries, and make new contributions to maintaining the security and stability of the Mekong River Basin.
