Chengdu "Panda Planet" and giant panda breeding research base expansion project started
Xinhua News Agency, Chengdu, September 27 (Reporter Li Qianwei) Rich giant panda culture theme tourism route, the panda base in the future can accommodate 180 giant pandas. "Panda Planet" and giant panda breeding research base expansion project officially started in Chengdu on the 25th, which means that Chengdu planning to build the "Panda Capital" project officially launched.
According to the plan, the "Panda Capital" built in Chengdu consists of three areas in the North Lake area, the Dujiangyan area and the Longquan Mountain area, with an area of 69 square kilometers.
The plan combines the ecological and cultural value of giant pandas with the construction of Chengdu's beautiful livable park city to create an ecological home for giant pandas.
"Panda Planet" belongs to the North Lake area, covers an area of 35 square kilometers, combined with industrial planning, will form a "1 + N + X" regional spatial structure.
One core attraction is the renovation and expansion project of the giant panda breeding research base; N cultural tourism consumption scenarios are created, namely, panda town, perimeter garden, dream garden, etc.; X-area infrastructure facilities.
After the renovation and expansion of the Chengdu Giant Panda Breeding Research Base, the scale will reach 3,525 mu, and the overall positioning will be a world-class giant panda protection demonstration site, and people and animals will share good times.
The park is planned to accommodate 180 giant pandas and their companion animals (little pandas and golden monkeys).
