Taiwanese scholars suggest: "Indeterminate years", Taiwanese businesses need to keep up with the development of mainstream industries in the mainland
The "2019 Taiwan Business Innovation and Operation Model Forum" was held in Taipei for two consecutive days on the 26th and 27th.
The event invited a number of Taiwanese business representatives and scholars to share their experiences on enterprise transformation, innovation, succession and market development.
The forum was organized by the Taipei Management Research Institute, and was co-organized by Qunyi Jinding Securities, the Outstanding Mainland Taiwan Business Association and other organizations.
The two-day meeting was divided into many seminars such as transformation and upgrading mode and business strategy, and more than 100 people attended the meeting.
Chen Mingzhang, president of the Taipei Institute of Management, said that Sino (mainland) U.S. trade frictions continue, and Taiwanese businesses are facing "uncertain years."
He believes that Taiwanese businesses need to keep pace with the times and keep up with the mainstream industries developed on the mainland, paying special attention to innovative products related to science and technology, culture, tourism and health.
"In the past, Taiwan businessmen paid attention to quality, effectiveness and delivery."
Chen Mingzhang believes that the above conditions of Taiwanese businesses alone are no longer enough.
He pointed out that Taiwan-funded enterprises should have both speed and service, speed up the supply chain, and attach importance to extended services and life products and services.
In addition, "service value-added" is also a new area that Taiwanese companies can vigorously develop.
During the speech, Xu Wentang, chairman of Taiwan Merchants Electronics Co., Ltd. from Guangdong, said that Amei Electronics had caused operational difficulties due to the sharp decline in orders, and the Group began to improve its business from many aspects such as structural adjustment and activation assets.
Retiring the traditional electrical appliance business, transforming the vehicle electronic equipment, and entering the smart home appliance industry, it took three years for the company to achieve revenue.
Bai Hongzhang, general manager of Sun God (Zhuhai) Electronics Co., Ltd., proposed that if it is difficult to develop new customers, it is better to focus on the original customer to provide "one-stop" services.
Customers replace the supplier by the poor service, high price, low quality, slow delivery speed, less variety, integrity of the six factors, as long as the solution of these six points, coupled with the timely transformation of the production line, the expansion of product categories, the company will become a customer can not replace the supplier.
