New regulations for comments: social capital needs to be qualified to obtain rural land management rights
Social capital needs to be qualified to obtain rural land management rights
The "Administrative Measures for the Transfer of Rural Land Management Rights" is intended to supervise the transfer of social capital to obtain land management rights such as industrial and commercial enterprises.
Yesterday, the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Affairs website issued a notice on the "Rural Land Management Measures for the Transfer of Rights to Work (Revised Draft for Comment)" (hereinafter referred to as the "Draft for Comment") for public comments, increasing the supervision and risk prevention of social capital transfer rights to obtain land management rights by industrial and commercial enterprises.
The draft opinion is now open to the public for comment.
The Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Affairs said that in order to implement the newly revised "Rural Land Contracting Law", further consolidate and improve the basic rural management system, deepen the reform of the rural land system, and implement the "three rights separation" system, the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Affairs revised the "Measures for the transfer and management of rural land contracting rights", forming the "Draft of Opinions".
The Beijing Youth Daily reporter learned that the "Draft of Opinions" released for the first time has many important changes.
The newly revised "Rural Land Contracting Law" clarified the scope of land transfer, implemented the concept of "separation of powers", and set up "land contracting management rights" and "land management rights" respectively, and made a clear distinction between the transfer of land contracting management rights, swaps and the transfer of land management rights (rent, subcontracting, shareholding or other methods).
In the "Draft Opinions", in order to implement the concept of "separation of powers", effectively respond to the main purpose of the "Rural Land Contracting Law" revision law, and take into account the large differences between the transfer of land management rights and the exchange of land contracting rights, transfer of land contracting rights, transfer of the parties, procedures, supervision, etc. The revised draft defines the scope of the transfer, focusing on the transfer of land management rights, the means of transfer, including rent, shareholding, etc.
For the transfer and exchange of land contracting management rights, administrative measures will be introduced separately.
The "Draft of Opinions" pointed out that in the context of the "three rights separation", farmers only have the right to land management for a certain period of time.
In theory, even if there is a bankruptcy liquidation, the farmer only has the risk of losing a certain period of business rights, so it is not necessary to provide for the return of the original contractor to the contractor of the contract, and there is a conflict with the Bankruptcy Law.
In order to prevent the risk of land loss for farmers, priority stocks, first-leasing and then-share-back methods have been generated in practice.
Considering that preferred stocks have a more mature theoretical discussion in company law, it is recommended to use it as an advocacy provision to prevent the risk of losing land.
